</div>
<div class="article-section">
	The site launched on 16/08/24.
	Give and Grow is still in it’s early stages as a CIC and has not yet fully launched as a program to the public. Thanks to the website, they have successfully recruited a Safeguarding officer.
	Give and Grow continues to seek tutors and other volunteers to help it’s running. Please visit the website, or contact Eva Mamphilly for more details.
	<div class="btn row">
		<a class="btn primary" href="https://giveandgrowcic.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Visit Give &amp; Grow<i class="ri-arrow-right-s-fill"></i></a>
		<a class="btn primary" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/eva-mampilly-755476284/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Contact Eva<i class="ri-arrow-right-s-fill"></i></a>
	</div>
</div>

<h2 id="challenges">Challenges</h2>
<div class="article-section">
	I came into this CIC at its earliest stages and had to be prepared for big changes throughout the process. The structure of the site, its funding structure and its members would all change during my time working on it.
	Initial wireframes showed a news section, which had to be removed for the site launch as we had no news to share yet and no blog-writer on board. The idea of including LinkedIn embeds was floated, but not within the scope of the official LinkedIn API that we had access to. We also lost our social media writer during this time.
	The news section was switched out for an Open Roles section, as we thought it would be more appropriate to highlight the fact that we were actively recruiting.
	<div class="btn row">
		<a class="btn primary" href="https://reachvolunteering.org.uk/org/give-and-grow-cic" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View Open Roles<i class="ri-arrow-right-s-fill"></i></a>
	</div>
</div>

<h2 id="initial-designs">Initial Designs</h2>
<div class="article-section">
	I initially met founder Eva Mamphilly via Zoom, where we discussed the purpose of the site and some potential visuals. Eva passed on a moodboard and web structure to me and I got to work on some basic layouts.
	{{ alpineCarousel({ carouselId: "initialCarousel",
					images: [
						{src:"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/landing-sticky.webp"},
						{src:"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/landing-edit.webp"},
						{src:"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/about.webp"},
						{src:"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/students.webp"},
						{src:"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/tutors.webp"},
						{src:"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/news.webp"},
						{src:"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/contact.webp"}
						],
					orientation: "slides-vert" 
				}) 
	}}
	Based on the initial moodboard, I created a higher fidelity version of the landing page. Colour contrast has to be increased from the original palette to meet readability guidelines.
	{{ gallery ({
		galleryId: "moodboardGallery",
		images: [
			"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/Moodboard.webp",
			"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/Mid-FiLanding.webp"
		]
	})}}
	We met again to discuss these designs and the wireframes were approved. The landing page pass proved useful as the client realised that she wanted to take the sites visuals in a different direction, stating that the original palette and mountain motif looked too mature for our target audience of secondary school students and university candidates.
</div>

<h2 id="branding">Branding</h2>
<div class="article-section">
	The client sent me an updated, basic landing page image with more of a “pop” colour scheme. She also sent me a diagram demonstrating the organisations funding system.*
	*subject to change
	With this new colour scheme and “doodle” style in mind I took another pass at the landing page, merging Illustrator-drawn doodles and stock images to form a more unique, on-brand look.
	{{ alpineCarousel({ carouselId: "newSchemeCarousel",
					images: [
						{src:"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/colour-scheme-2.webp",
						caption: "Sketch with updated colour scheme provided by Eva"},
						{src:"assets/images/case-studies/Give-and-Grow/Completed/homepage.webp",
						caption: "Updated homepage based on sketches"}
						],
					orientation: "slides-vert" 
				}) 
	}}
	For more information on the graphic and brand design, please visit the Graphics Gallery.
	<div class="btn row">
		<a class="btn primary" href="{{'/web-design/Give-And-Grow/graphic-gallery/' | toAbsoluteUrl}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View Graphic Gallery<i class="ri-arrow-right-s-fill"></i></a>
	</div>
</div>


<h2 id="research">Research</h2>
<h3 id="user-personas">User Personas</h3>
<div class="article-section">
	Before expanding this initial design, it was important to outline the target audience. I created some personas, keeping the info provided by the founder in mind.
</div>
	{{ personas({
		personas: [
			{
				icon: "ri-hand-heart-fill",
